8 An Act relating to waters and water rights; amending
27A O.S. 2021, Section 2-6-103.1, which relates to
9 contracts for technical assistance programs;
authorizing the Department of Environmental Quality
10 to contract with certain suppliers; authorizing the
Department to use a portion of certain funds to
11 contract with certain parties; and providing an
effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 27A O.S. 2021, Section 2-6-103.1,
16 is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 2-6-103.1. The Department of Environmental Quality may,
18 to the extent funds are available, contract with the Oklahoma Rural
19 Water Association or qualified state suppliers for technical
20 assistance programs to rural water and wastewater system operators
21 throughout the state. The Department may use a portion of the funds
22 appropriated for grants and assistance programs to rural water and
23 small systems to contract with qualified state suppliers to provide
24 technical assistance programs to rural water and wastewater system
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4246 Page 1

1 oper ators throughout the state. Assistance in response to drinking
2 water or wastewater emergencies is also eligible. The Department
3 may contract with other nonprofit entities in addition to the
4 Oklahoma Rural Water Association or qualified state suppliers for
5 this purpose if the Department, in its discretion, determines that
6 those entities can and will provide equally effective and efficient
7 technical assistance services to rural water and wastewater system
8 operators throughout the state.
9 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
10 Passed the House of Representatives the 23rd day of March, 2026.
